Use of Information:
As a general policy no personally identifiable information, such as your name, address, or e-mail address, is automatically collected by Cara from your visit to the Site and/or use the Services. However, certain non-personal information is recorded by the standard operation of Cara’s internet servers. Information such as the type of browser being used, any mobile devices being used, operating systems in use, device IDs, and your IP address may be gathered in order to enhance your online experience. If you sign up for Cara’s online community, we may collect information about the people, accounts, and groups you are connected to and how you interact with them across the Cara Site, such as people you communicate with, how you communicate with them and/or the works of Art And Other User Generated Content and/or interests you share in common. We may use such information for things like helping you and others find people you may know and for connecting you to share and enhance your experiences within Cara. We may also, in limited circumstances, request your phone number for purposes of account verification or authentication. In such circumstance, your number will only be used one time for that limited purpose and will not be saved. We will not collect any other data or other information stored in or connected with those apps as part of this process. Any such information will only be used to enhance your experience with the Cara Site and/or to improve the Cara Site and the Services Cara offers.
The Cara Site’s various mailing lists, downloads, special offers, contests, registration forms, and surveys may request that you give us contact information such as your name, mailing and/or e-mail address; demographic information such as your age and gender; and personal preference information such as your tastes in artwork or interests. Any such personally identifiable information will never be sold or leased to any third parties. Information submitted at the time of submission will, instead, be used by Cara only solely as necessary for our legitimate business interests, including without limitation the improvement of our products, services and the contents of the Cara Site. The type of personally identifiable information collected will vary depending upon the activity and may include your first and last name; e-mail address; account information for certain third-party sites or networks, such as Facebook, Instagram, and Twitter, and/or location. We may also collect the contact information of your friends if you choose to connect your social network accounts with your account with Cara and/or with your login credentials to your social network accounts with your account with Cara. Cara may also share such information with our business and promotional partners to further those interests but, as noted above, such information will never be sold or leased to any third parties. With your permission, we may use your contact information to send you information about Cara and its products. You may always opt-out of receiving future mailings as provided below. Cara does not store any credit card information it may receive in regard to a specific transaction except as necessary to complete and satisfy its rights and obligations with regard to such transaction.
Cara may disclose user information in special cases when we have reason to believe that disclosing this information is necessary to identify, contact or bring legal action against someone who may be causing injury to or interference (either intentionally or unintentionally) with Cara’s rights or property, other users of the Cara Site and/or any Art And Other User Generated Content displayed on the Cara Site , or anyone else that could be harmed by such activities.
Children Age 13 and Under:
Cara recognizes the special obligation to protect personally identifiable information obtained from children age 13 and under. AS SUCH, IF YOU ARE 13 YEARS OLD OR YOUNGER, CARA REQUESTS THAT YOU NOT SUBMIT ANY PERSONAL INFORMATION TO THE SITE AND/OR TO CARA. If Cara discovers that a child age 13 or younger has provided us with personally identifiable information, we will delete that child’s personally identifiable information from our records.
Use of Cookies:
Cookies are pieces of information that a website transfers to an individual’s computer hard drive for record keeping purposes. Cookies make using our Cara Site easier by, among other things, saving your passwords and preferences for you. These cookies are restricted for use only on our Cara Site, and do not transfer any personal information to any other party. Most browsers are initially set up to accept cookies. You can, however, reset your browser to refuse all cookies or indicate when a cookie is being sent. Please consult the technical information relevant to your browser for instructions. If you choose to disable your cookies setting or refuse to accept a cookie, some parts of the Cara Site may not function properly or may be considerably slower.
