Security/How Your Personally Identifiable Information Is Protected:
Security for all personally identifiable information is extremely important to us. We have implemented technical, administrative and physical security measures to attempt to protect your personally identifiable information from unauthorized access and improper use. We also protect your personally identifiable information offline. Only employees who need the information to perform a specific job (for example, user service) are granted access to personally identifiable information. The computers/servers in which we store personally identifiable information are kept in a secure environment. We continually review all such measures and update them when appropriate. Unfortunately, no data transmission over the Internet can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. As a result, while we strive to protect your personal information, Cara cannot ensure or warrant the security of any information you transmit via the internet. By transmitting any such information to Cara, you accept that you do so at your own risk.
Choice/Opt-Out:
The Cara Site may provide you the opportunity to opt-in to receive communications from us at the point where we request information about you. You always have the option of removing your name from any e-mail list in order to discontinue any such future communications. In order to ensure immediate removal from any list, please follow the specific instructions set forth within the communications you receive from Cara which you no longer wish to receive. If you are unsuccessful in completing the instructions specified in any such communication, please e-mail us at privacy@cara.app, including a copy of the undesired email attached to the request, and state you wish to be removed from the mailing list.
Your Access to and Control Over Your Personally Identifiable Information:
At any time, but only once per calendar year, or as otherwise required under applicable law, users may contact Cara to review the personally identifiable information that Cara has collected about you. If you discover any errors, please notify Cara and the information will be corrected. To review the personally identifiable information that Cara has collected about you, please send an email to privacy@cara.app with the subject line: “Personal Information Review Request.” Users may also request that Cara delete a user account(s) or, if you have not established a user account, your email address, and any related data at any time. If you wish to delete your user account(s), please email us at privacy@cara.app with the words “Delete Account” in the subject line. If you do not have a user account and wish to delete your email address or other personally identifiable information that you might have provided through your use of the Cara Site, and/or any Services, please email us at privacy@cara.app with the words “Delete My Information” in the subject line.
Retention:
We will save your personal data until you erase your user account or otherwise exercise your right to erase your personal data as provided above.
Transfer of Information Across National Borders:
Our site and various information we collect regarding the Services and/or Art And Other User Generated Content are operated on servers located in various jurisdictions, including the United States. When you access or use the Cara Site, the Services, and/or any Art And Other User Generated Content, personal information about you may be transferred outside the country in which you are situated to these other locations. Cara’s company policies ensure that such personal information is protected to the same standard when processed by any Cara entity or office around the world. We also ensure that appropriate contracts containing standard data protection clauses approved by the European Commission to protect that information and the rights of individuals are in place with any and all third-party service providers we may use.
Your California Privacy Rights:
California law and the laws of other states and countries permits residents of those jurisdictions to request from companies conducting business in California a list of third parties to which the company has disclosed personally identifiable information during the preceding year for direct marketing purposes as well as other details regarding types of information collected and how it is used, as well as other information. Cara has not and will not share your personally identifiable information with third parties for their direct marketing purposes; accordingly, it will not maintain such a list of third parties. If you are a resident of California or any other state or country with a similar and want additional information confirming how Cara does not share your personally identifiable information with third parties for their direct marketing purposes, or additional details regarding information that is collected, you may contact us at privacy@cara.app with the words “California Privacy” (or the jurisdiction that is applicable) in the subject line of your email.
